WEBVTT

00:01.418 --> 00:02.878
NARRATOR:
Previously on
When Calls the Heart:

00:02.878 --> 00:04.129
I'm your replacement.

00:04.129 --> 00:05.881
A letter
in your employment file

00:05.881 --> 00:08.216
was brought to my attention.
I was forced to replace you.

00:08.216 --> 00:10.302
Do you remember
Superintendent Thomas Higgins?

00:10.302 --> 00:11.720
He isn't what
he seems.

00:11.720 --> 00:13.388
I'm sorry, I can't
help you, Elizabeth.

00:13.388 --> 00:15.975
Jack. A telegram came in
from Mountie Headquarters.

00:15.975 --> 00:18.268
It's Doug. He was killed
in the line of duty.

00:19.394 --> 00:21.062
ELIZABETH:
"Sometimes, we forget

00:21.062 --> 00:22.731
"how precious life is.

00:22.731 --> 00:25.233
"Douglas Burke died a hero.

00:25.233 --> 00:27.611
"Jack rode out
for the funeral today.

00:27.611 --> 00:30.197
"I know he hurts inside,

00:30.197 --> 00:31.991
"but it's more than that.

00:31.991 --> 00:34.743
"Even though
this is all part of a plan

00:34.743 --> 00:36.411
"greater than all of us,

00:36.411 --> 00:39.957
"I worry that Jack blames
himself for Doug's death

00:39.957 --> 00:43.585
and it breaks my heart to
watch him carry that burden."

00:44.920 --> 00:46.922
I offered to go
to the funeral with Jack,

00:46.922 --> 00:48.549
but he said he wanted
to be alone.

00:48.549 --> 00:49.967
Sometimes,
I think it's harder

00:49.967 --> 00:52.845
for men to grieve
than it is for women.

00:52.845 --> 00:55.014
Doug was so young.

00:55.014 --> 00:57.016
It really isn't fair.

00:58.141 --> 00:59.977
SHANE:
Miss Thatcher?

00:59.977 --> 01:01.603
Good morning,
Mr. Cantrell.

01:01.603 --> 01:03.480
I wanted to thank you
for letting my boy

01:03.480 --> 01:06.107
study with the rest
of the kids after school.

01:06.107 --> 01:08.360
He took it pretty hard
when Mr. Stoneman expelled him.

01:08.360 --> 01:11.947
Mr. Stoneman
made a mistake.

01:11.947 --> 01:14.366
I sure wish you were teaching
in that classroom again.

01:14.366 --> 01:16.618
Philip misses being there
with all the kids.

01:16.618 --> 01:18.328
I do too.

01:18.328 --> 01:20.831
But we'll see the two of you
at the music recital?

01:20.831 --> 01:22.082
We'll be there.

01:22.082 --> 01:25.293
[♪♪♪]

01:25.293 --> 01:26.837
What is it?

01:27.963 --> 01:31.050
I feel like
I'm drifting away.

01:31.050 --> 01:33.010
How so?

01:33.010 --> 01:35.178
[SIGHS]
It isn't the same,

01:35.178 --> 01:37.222
being a tutor
and not a teacher.

01:37.222 --> 01:39.600
I'm just a volunteer
who works with the kids

01:39.600 --> 01:41.142
for a couple of hours
after school.

01:41.142 --> 01:42.811
You're still making
a difference.

01:42.811 --> 01:44.605
I'm helping them
with their studies,

01:44.605 --> 01:46.023
but that's
one small piece

01:46.023 --> 01:48.316
of what a teacher
really does.

01:48.316 --> 01:49.735
I know.

01:49.735 --> 01:52.153
Cody misses you
so much.

01:52.153 --> 01:54.823
But it won't be
like this forever.

01:56.033 --> 01:58.035
What if it is?

01:58.035 --> 02:00.996
Elizabeth, you will
get your job back.

02:00.996 --> 02:02.748
Just be patient.

02:02.748 --> 02:05.834
Hmm. It isn't easy.

02:10.130 --> 02:13.842
[♪♪♪]

02:18.680 --> 02:22.350
It means so much to me
that you're here, Jack.

02:22.350 --> 02:24.561
Anything for you and Doug.

02:27.064 --> 02:30.191
COLLINS:
Corporal Douglas Burke
was a true hero.

02:30.191 --> 02:34.154
He served his country
with honor and dignity.

02:34.154 --> 02:37.532
As Mounties,
we swear an oath

02:37.532 --> 02:39.409
to live up
to that high ideal,

02:39.409 --> 02:41.120
no matter
the personal sacrifice.

02:41.120 --> 02:43.664
And Doug paid
the ultimate sacrifice,

02:43.664 --> 02:45.791
but he did so
valiantly and bravely.

02:45.791 --> 02:49.003
He led the life
he was born to lead.

02:49.003 --> 02:51.130
He followed his destiny.

02:51.130 --> 02:54.424
No life can be better lived
than that.

02:56.885 --> 02:58.595
MOUNTIE:
Bullet. Salute!

02:58.595 --> 03:00.806
Present arm.

03:00.806 --> 03:01.890
Fire!

03:02.891 --> 03:04.893
Reload.
[CHAMBERS LOADING]

03:04.893 --> 03:06.561
Present.
[GUNS CLICK]

03:06.561 --> 03:08.355
Fire!
[GUNS SHOOT]

03:08.355 --> 03:09.982
Reload.

03:09.982 --> 03:11.316
Present.

03:11.316 --> 03:13.234
Fire.
[GUNS SHOOT]

03:13.234 --> 03:15.362
Order arms.

03:21.160 --> 03:23.787
[TRUMPET PLAYING]

03:53.441 --> 03:56.611
[♪♪♪]

04:06.955 --> 04:09.249
[♪♪♪]

04:26.683 --> 04:28.936
[♪♪♪]

04:34.441 --> 04:36.235
ELIZABETH:
Jack.

04:46.578 --> 04:48.830
Is there anything I can do?

04:48.830 --> 04:50.707
That hug was a good start.

04:53.418 --> 04:55.754
I can't believe Doug's gone.

04:55.754 --> 04:57.589
You were
a good friend to him.

04:57.589 --> 04:59.091
I could have done more.

04:59.091 --> 05:00.550
Should've done more.

05:00.550 --> 05:02.469
[FOOTSTEPS]

05:02.469 --> 05:04.221
Oh, Jack.
I'm so sorry

05:04.221 --> 05:06.306
to hear
about what happened.

05:06.306 --> 05:08.475
I can't imagine what
you must be feeling.

05:08.475 --> 05:10.227
I appreciate that, Rosie.

05:10.227 --> 05:12.562
Well, I didn't mean
to interrupt,

05:12.562 --> 05:14.064
but these are for you.

05:14.064 --> 05:16.357
I hope the little urchins
like apple pie.

05:16.357 --> 05:18.359
I was debating
between apple and cherry,

05:18.359 --> 05:20.403
but cherry stains
are so difficult to get out,

05:20.403 --> 05:22.197
but then I thought--
Don't worry, Rosemary.

05:22.197 --> 05:24.908
I'm sure they'll love it.
Thank you.

05:24.908 --> 05:27.661
I have tutoring.
I'll see you later?

05:27.661 --> 05:29.454
Sure.

05:29.454 --> 05:32.499
[♪♪♪]

05:32.499 --> 05:34.835
None of my teachers
ever brought me pie.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.419
[CHUCKLES]

05:36.419 --> 05:38.379
It's for
her math lesson.

05:38.379 --> 05:40.966
You know Elizabeth.
Always finding new ways

05:40.966 --> 05:44.178
to stimulate
those eager young minds.

05:44.178 --> 05:47.139
I've never met anyone
so devoted to their work.

05:47.139 --> 05:48.807
I know just what you mean.

05:48.807 --> 05:50.475
It isn't just a job
for her, is it?

05:50.475 --> 05:53.687
Something she lives
and breathes.

05:59.276 --> 06:03.238
Who is ready
for fractions?

06:03.238 --> 06:05.324
I don't
understand them at all!

06:05.324 --> 06:09.536
Well, fractions
are everywhere you look.

06:09.536 --> 06:12.622
Robert, could you please
pass these out?

06:16.126 --> 06:18.295
Ta-da!

06:18.295 --> 06:21.048
I think
I'm gonna like fractions.

06:21.048 --> 06:22.924
There are eight of you,

06:22.924 --> 06:24.718
so I am going to cut this pie

06:24.718 --> 06:29.764
into eight equal sections.

06:29.764 --> 06:32.100
If I remove one piece...

06:33.768 --> 06:36.938
how many eighths
do we have left?

06:38.023 --> 06:38.982
Seven.

06:38.982 --> 06:40.399
ELIZABETH:
That's right!

06:40.399 --> 06:42.652
Eight-eighths minus one-eighth
equals...?

06:42.652 --> 06:43.987
KIDS:
Seven-eighths.

06:43.987 --> 06:45.989
Seven-eighths.
That's right!

06:45.989 --> 06:48.283
You just learned
how to subtract fractions,

06:48.283 --> 06:50.327
and it was easy as pie.

06:50.327 --> 06:51.578
Do we all get to have some?

06:51.578 --> 06:53.247
Yes, you all get to have some.

06:55.582 --> 06:57.959
Uh, Cody...

06:57.959 --> 06:59.627
you may serve everyone.

06:59.627 --> 07:01.338
[STONEMAN CLEARS THROAT]

07:05.384 --> 07:07.135
I see
you're tutoring the children.

07:07.135 --> 07:08.803
ELIZABETH:
They asked for my help.

07:09.804 --> 07:12.099
It seems to be...
working.

07:12.099 --> 07:13.641
I'm glad you noticed.

07:13.641 --> 07:16.395
Yes. Even Mr. Cantrell
seems to be doing better.

07:17.354 --> 07:19.940
[♪♪♪]

07:22.276 --> 07:23.860
I was thinking,

07:23.860 --> 07:26.029
if I can catch him up
on his reading and writing,

07:26.029 --> 07:28.448
maybe you could let him
back into school.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.450
I'm afraid
that would take a miracle.

07:30.450 --> 07:33.120
I believe in miracles.

07:33.120 --> 07:36.206
[SNIFFS]
Good day, Miss Thatcher.

07:43.504 --> 07:46.091
[PIANO PLAYING]

07:52.806 --> 07:54.599
Have you decided
what you're going to play

07:54.599 --> 07:55.600
for the recital, Timmy?

07:55.600 --> 07:57.144
"Danny Boy."

07:57.144 --> 07:59.104
You know that's
Mountie Jack's favorite song?

07:59.104 --> 08:00.939
My dad's too,
but I can't play

08:00.939 --> 08:02.316
unless you sing with me.

08:02.316 --> 08:03.400
You promised.

08:03.400 --> 08:06.361
Don't you worry.
I will be there.

08:06.361 --> 08:07.946
Once we get
the depot built,

08:07.946 --> 08:09.614
we'll start
laying track right away.

08:09.614 --> 08:11.325
Shouldn't
be a problem.

08:11.325 --> 08:13.493
I'm in the mood for a drink.
You want to join me?

08:13.493 --> 08:16.496
Oh, dear. I'm afraid
that won't be possible.

08:16.496 --> 08:17.956
Not today, anyway.

08:17.956 --> 08:20.375
Or any afternoon this week.
Or next.

08:20.375 --> 08:21.626
Why not?

08:21.626 --> 08:23.170
The saloon is closed
until 4:00,

08:23.170 --> 08:25.380
after Elizabeth is done
working with the children,

08:25.380 --> 08:28.258
which won't be for
another, uh, 40 minutes.

08:28.258 --> 08:30.260
Miss Thatcher is teaching
in the saloon?

08:30.260 --> 08:32.720
Well, she is a teacher.

08:32.720 --> 08:33.721
She was dismissed!

08:33.721 --> 08:35.265
Oh, goodness.

08:35.265 --> 08:37.100
There's no reason
to get so upset.

08:37.100 --> 08:38.893
She's simply
helping the children

08:38.893 --> 08:40.145
prepare for a test.

08:40.145 --> 08:41.355
That's Mr. Stoneman's job.

08:41.355 --> 08:43.023
Yes, it is,
but apparently,

08:43.023 --> 08:45.317
he isn't
doing it very well at all.

08:45.317 --> 08:47.902
Good day, Mr. Wyatt.
Mr. Avery.

08:49.737 --> 08:51.531
Did you
know about this?

08:51.531 --> 08:53.200
No.
But I did warn you

08:53.200 --> 08:54.659
that firing Elizabeth Thatcher

08:54.659 --> 08:56.411
wouldn't be popular
with a lot of people.

08:56.411 --> 08:58.079
I don't care how people feel.

08:58.079 --> 09:00.415
I don't want that woman
teaching anyone, anywhere.

09:06.087 --> 09:07.506
ELIZABETH:
It's getting late.

09:07.506 --> 09:09.549
I thought
you might like something to eat.

09:09.549 --> 09:11.676
I'm not hungry, thanks.

09:14.513 --> 09:16.306
Jack...

09:16.306 --> 09:19.559
I don't pretend to know
how you feel, but...

09:19.559 --> 09:22.437
I'm here,
if you want to talk.

09:22.437 --> 09:24.356
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

09:30.111 --> 09:31.988
I hope I'm not
interrupting.

09:31.988 --> 09:33.323
No, sir.

09:33.323 --> 09:36.284
I'm escorting
Mrs. Burke back home,

09:36.284 --> 09:38.412
and she asked
to see you.

09:38.412 --> 09:39.620
Please.

09:39.620 --> 09:41.206
Thank you, Jack.

09:42.790 --> 09:45.877
Oh, no need.
I'll wait outside.

09:49.381 --> 09:51.132
I'm Elizabeth Thatcher,
Mrs. Burke,

09:51.132 --> 09:53.634
and I am so very sorry
for your loss.

09:53.634 --> 09:55.178
Douglas wrote
about meeting you.

09:55.178 --> 09:57.180
He said that you were
very kind to him.

09:58.306 --> 09:59.640
I'll leave you two alone.

09:59.640 --> 10:00.641
Oh, no.

10:00.641 --> 10:02.394
I'd like you to stay.

10:03.395 --> 10:04.687
Of course.

10:05.980 --> 10:07.148
Jack...

10:10.818 --> 10:12.779
I have something for you.

10:14.364 --> 10:16.533
[CHAIN CLINKING SOFTLY]

10:16.533 --> 10:18.785
[♪♪♪]

10:18.785 --> 10:20.870
The Saint Christopher medal
I gave Doug

10:20.870 --> 10:22.581
the day he graduated.

10:22.581 --> 10:25.041
Douglas was an only child.

10:25.041 --> 10:28.002
He came to think of Jack
as his big brother,

10:28.002 --> 10:30.755
and I think of you
as my second son,

10:30.755 --> 10:32.048
which is why I know

10:32.048 --> 10:33.925
he would want you
to have this.

10:33.925 --> 10:35.218
Wouldn't be right.

10:35.218 --> 10:36.928
It couldn't be more right.

10:42.434 --> 10:44.561
I should've been there, Helen.

10:45.770 --> 10:47.855
Doug went in my place.

10:50.775 --> 10:52.735
Please forgive me.

10:52.735 --> 10:54.404
Oh...

10:54.404 --> 10:57.574
My Doug's death
isn't your fault.

10:57.574 --> 10:59.451
He wanted to lead those men.

10:59.451 --> 11:01.286
If I'd gone, he'd...

11:01.286 --> 11:02.579
He might still be alive.

11:02.579 --> 11:04.789
God has a plan for us.

11:04.789 --> 11:07.292
I don't understand it,

11:07.292 --> 11:10.170
but I know
my Doug was happy

11:10.170 --> 11:13.798
because God called him
to do what he was doing,

11:13.798 --> 11:16.134
and that...

11:16.134 --> 11:18.470
that brings me peace.

11:21.014 --> 11:22.557
Jack...

11:22.557 --> 11:26.394
I pray you are granted
peace too, Jack.

11:28.896 --> 11:31.650
[♪♪♪]

11:33.985 --> 11:36.237
Can you explain
why the Thatcher woman

11:36.237 --> 11:38.114
is working with
the children after school?

11:38.114 --> 11:39.574
Yes. She is helping

11:39.574 --> 11:42.661
the ones who are behind
in their studies.

11:42.661 --> 11:44.954
The regional exams
are in a few days.

11:44.954 --> 11:48.500
Forgive me for stating
the obvious, Mr. Stoneman,

11:48.500 --> 11:50.960
but isn't that your job?

11:52.128 --> 11:54.214
It is, but I see
no harm in Miss--

11:54.214 --> 11:55.756
Elizabeth Thatcher

11:55.756 --> 11:58.468
is trying to cause trouble
for the railroad.

11:58.468 --> 12:01.513
I don't want to see her
near those children again.

12:01.513 --> 12:04.391
You find a way to teach them
so they don't need her,

12:04.391 --> 12:06.351
or I'll find someone who can.

12:08.144 --> 12:11.648
[♪♪♪]

12:17.529 --> 12:19.698
We have to talk.

12:23.742 --> 12:25.744
Yes, sir, we do.

12:29.832 --> 12:32.335
[♪♪♪]

12:35.338 --> 12:38.383
Is it really so bad up north
that you have to go?

12:38.383 --> 12:40.051
It's worse.

12:40.051 --> 12:42.970
The syndicates, the gangs,
they're not going away.

12:44.180 --> 12:45.515
Did you tell Elizabeth?

12:45.515 --> 12:47.892
No. Not yet.

12:47.892 --> 12:49.852
[SIGHS]

12:49.852 --> 12:52.480
Not until
I make a final decision.

12:54.399 --> 12:56.901
We all have a code, Jack...

12:59.862 --> 13:02.574
You have to do
what's right for you.

13:06.578 --> 13:08.705
[SIGHS]

13:08.705 --> 13:10.789
[♪♪♪]

13:10.789 --> 13:12.417
What is this?

13:12.417 --> 13:13.752
Don't be mad,
Miss Thatcher,

13:13.752 --> 13:15.836
but we didn't
do our homework.

13:15.836 --> 13:17.338
I'm not mad,

13:17.338 --> 13:19.633
I just hope
you have a very good reason.

13:19.633 --> 13:20.717
We wrote
letters instead!

13:20.717 --> 13:22.009
What kind of letters?

13:22.009 --> 13:23.720
ROBERT:
Good letters,
'cause we heard

13:23.720 --> 13:24.929
a bad letter is why

13:24.929 --> 13:26.556
you can't
be our teacher anymore.

13:26.556 --> 13:28.849
Every kid in school wrote one.

13:28.849 --> 13:32.270
We want to tell the Mayor
how much we need you back.

13:33.896 --> 13:35.440
I don't know what to say.

13:35.440 --> 13:37.400
And if the letters
don't work,

13:37.400 --> 13:40.987
the parents have decided
to start our own school

13:40.987 --> 13:43.531
and pay your salary
ourselves.

13:43.531 --> 13:46.242
It'll be like when
you first came to town.

13:46.242 --> 13:48.328
You can have
your classes here.

13:48.328 --> 13:51.331
I can't tell you
how much that means to me,

13:51.331 --> 13:53.583
and how flattered I am.

13:54.875 --> 13:56.377
So you'll do it?

13:56.377 --> 13:58.797
I wish I could,
but I can't.

13:58.797 --> 14:01.174
What? Why not?

14:01.174 --> 14:03.802
ELIZABETH:
Well, even if we start
our own school,

14:03.802 --> 14:05.804
it won't clear my name.

14:07.972 --> 14:10.141
But you'd still
be teaching the children.

14:10.141 --> 14:12.018
And nothing would
mean more to me,

14:12.018 --> 14:14.312
nothing
in the whole wide world.

14:14.312 --> 14:16.481
But you're going to grow up,

14:16.481 --> 14:18.983
and when you move on,
then where will I be?

14:18.983 --> 14:21.319
The new families
won't know me.

14:22.779 --> 14:25.198
I know I was born
to make a difference

14:25.198 --> 14:28.117
in the lives of the children
here in Hope Valley...

14:28.117 --> 14:30.578
Not just today, but...

14:30.578 --> 14:33.581
Tomorrow,
and the next day.

14:33.581 --> 14:36.835
I can't live without it.

14:38.586 --> 14:41.881
But what if
w-we can't live without you?

14:42.923 --> 14:45.218
[♪♪♪]

14:46.553 --> 14:48.221
Of course you can.

14:48.221 --> 14:50.598
You have your dad
to take care of you.

14:53.017 --> 14:55.186
And in the meantime,

14:55.186 --> 14:58.939
I need to fight to take back
what was taken from me.

14:58.939 --> 15:01.192
No matter how long it takes,

15:01.192 --> 15:02.694
or where it takes me.

15:02.694 --> 15:05.238
TIMMY:
How long will that be?

15:10.410 --> 15:12.078
I don't know,
sweetheart.

15:12.078 --> 15:14.414
But I won't leave
until after your exams,

15:14.414 --> 15:16.165
and after the recital.

15:16.165 --> 15:19.001
And I'll be back...
I promise.

15:20.545 --> 15:22.589
We still want you
to read these.

15:24.674 --> 15:25.800
Oh.

15:30.346 --> 15:31.972
Thank you.

15:33.600 --> 15:35.268
O-Oh!

15:35.268 --> 15:36.936
Oh-ho-ho-ho!

15:42.108 --> 15:44.110
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

15:46.195 --> 15:48.782
ELIZABETH:
"Miss Thatcher says
I can be anything I want.

15:48.782 --> 15:50.700
"I wanted to be
a bear doctor, heh,

15:50.700 --> 15:53.870
but now I want to be a teacher
who's as special as she is."

15:56.790 --> 15:58.583
Well, this one's
my favorite.

16:00.334 --> 16:02.211
From Philip.

16:02.211 --> 16:05.924
"Miss Thatcher thinks I'm smart,
so I think I'm smart too."

16:07.717 --> 16:10.261
You've made a real difference
in his life.

16:10.261 --> 16:12.597
In all of their lives.

16:12.597 --> 16:14.515
It's what I'm meant to do.

16:14.515 --> 16:16.559
[♪♪♪]

16:16.559 --> 16:18.436
Elizabeth...

16:19.979 --> 16:21.815
What happened to Doug...

16:21.815 --> 16:25.151
It's made me think about
what I'm meant to do.

16:25.151 --> 16:26.736
And?

16:26.736 --> 16:29.447
Collins has asked me
to lead a new division

16:29.447 --> 16:30.907
in the Northern Territories.

16:30.907 --> 16:32.909
Jack, no.

16:32.909 --> 16:34.285
No, it's too dangerous.

16:34.285 --> 16:37.037
You said teaching is
a part of who you are.

16:37.037 --> 16:38.038
Mm-hmm.

16:38.038 --> 16:39.958
Fighting the good fight...

16:39.958 --> 16:42.001
is who I am.

16:42.001 --> 16:43.586
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

16:43.586 --> 16:44.838
[GASP]

16:50.927 --> 16:52.428
Coming.

17:03.356 --> 17:05.274
Francine?

17:05.274 --> 17:07.401
[EXHALES]

17:07.401 --> 17:10.237
FRANCINE:
I know I should have
come sooner, but...

17:10.237 --> 17:12.198
at least
I'm here now.

17:12.198 --> 17:13.616
Everything
Miss Fessler says

17:13.616 --> 17:15.994
confirms what I told you
about Thomas Higgins.

17:15.994 --> 17:18.245
Which means you have
to reinstate Elizabeth

17:18.245 --> 17:19.747
as our school's
teacher.

17:19.747 --> 17:21.248
Can we all just slow down?

17:21.248 --> 17:22.834
As a benefactor
of the new school,

17:22.834 --> 17:24.669
I don't see why we should
believe this woman.

17:24.669 --> 17:27.421
Because she's telling
the truth.

17:27.421 --> 17:29.674
She's offered no proof
to support her claim

17:29.674 --> 17:31.425
that Mr. Higgins harassed her.

17:31.425 --> 17:32.719
Here's your proof.

17:32.719 --> 17:36.723
Higgins would
leave these on my desk.

17:36.723 --> 17:39.684
You can read for yourself
what he was suggesting.

17:41.394 --> 17:43.062
I think, if you
compare the handwriting

17:43.062 --> 17:44.355
to the writing
on the letter

17:44.355 --> 17:45.857
in Elizabeth's file,

17:45.857 --> 17:47.775
you'll find
they are the same.

17:52.238 --> 17:54.198
You either do
the right thing, Henry,

17:54.198 --> 17:56.075
or you'll face
a recall election.

17:56.075 --> 17:57.702
I'll make sure of it.

18:01.163 --> 18:05.043
Well, given this new evidence
that's been brought to light...

18:06.920 --> 18:09.213
Miss Thatcher,
you're reinstated as teacher.

18:09.213 --> 18:11.632
[♪♪♪]

18:11.632 --> 18:14.260
Heh.

18:14.260 --> 18:16.429
WYATT:
But if there's
any further corroboration

18:16.429 --> 18:18.097
of Thomas Higgins' claim
against you--

18:18.097 --> 18:20.099
Mr. Wyatt.
It's over...

18:20.099 --> 18:21.976
So drop it.

18:25.229 --> 18:27.732
Thank you, Francine.

18:27.732 --> 18:29.692
Thank you.

18:34.321 --> 18:36.240
Where will
you go from here?

18:36.240 --> 18:37.867
I'm not sure.

18:37.867 --> 18:40.411
I do know
that I won't work

18:40.411 --> 18:41.829
for the railroad again.

18:41.829 --> 18:43.205
Any man who treats teachers

18:43.205 --> 18:44.457
the way Wyatt treated you

18:44.457 --> 18:45.875
is not someone
I want to work for.

18:45.875 --> 18:47.877
I'm sorry
about what happened.

18:47.877 --> 18:49.169
Don't be.

18:49.169 --> 18:51.297
I've always
thought of life as...

18:51.297 --> 18:53.215
As an opportunity to learn,

18:53.215 --> 18:55.802
and you've taught me
a great deal.

18:55.802 --> 18:57.511
Such as?

18:57.511 --> 18:59.305
You've shown me...

18:59.305 --> 19:01.474
that children need more

19:01.474 --> 19:03.935
than just discipline
and repetition,

19:03.935 --> 19:05.812
that they're special.

19:05.812 --> 19:09.565
We need
more teachers like you.

19:09.565 --> 19:12.443
I wish you all the best,
Miss Thatcher.

19:12.443 --> 19:13.820
Thank you.

19:13.820 --> 19:15.029
Thank you.

19:20.910 --> 19:22.411
[HORSE SNORTS]

19:22.411 --> 19:24.080
I guess
this is goodbye.

19:24.080 --> 19:27.083
It was so brave of you
to come all this way.

19:27.083 --> 19:29.085
But I didn't
do it right away,

19:29.085 --> 19:30.461
and I should have.

19:30.461 --> 19:32.546
What made you
change your mind?

19:34.423 --> 19:35.925
This.

19:38.761 --> 19:41.514
[♪♪♪]

19:45.351 --> 19:46.519
[ELIZABETH CHUCKLES]

19:46.519 --> 19:48.228
Where did you get this?

19:48.228 --> 19:49.480
Didn't you send it?

19:49.480 --> 19:50.564
No.

19:50.564 --> 19:52.191
Well, somebody did,

19:52.191 --> 19:54.276
and when I saw
the happiness in your eyes,

19:54.276 --> 19:56.821
and the faces of
those sweet children...

19:56.821 --> 19:58.865
But it was the inscription
on the back

19:58.865 --> 20:01.034
that really
spoke to my heart.

20:01.034 --> 20:05.079
"Bad things happen
if good people do nothing."

20:05.079 --> 20:07.748
It was time for me
to do some good.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.168
Thank you.

20:20.011 --> 20:22.180
[HORSES NEIGH]

20:35.275 --> 20:37.486
You sent the photograph,
didn't you?

20:37.486 --> 20:39.238
As soon as you said
Francine was angry

20:39.238 --> 20:41.032
when you told her
what Higgins had done,

20:41.032 --> 20:43.076
I knew there was
more to her story.

20:43.076 --> 20:45.285
You're the best friend
in the world.

20:45.285 --> 20:47.914
Well, you are the best
teacher in the world.

20:47.914 --> 20:50.166
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

20:53.293 --> 20:54.837
[♪♪♪]

20:54.837 --> 20:56.797
JACK:
At Doug's funeral,

20:56.797 --> 20:59.217
Sam Collins said...

20:59.217 --> 21:03.179
every person has to live
the life they were born to lead.

21:03.179 --> 21:05.765
Every man has to live
his destiny.

21:08.308 --> 21:10.352
It was like
he was speaking to my soul.

21:11.896 --> 21:14.523
Well, then
you have to listen.

21:14.523 --> 21:16.192
I have.

21:16.192 --> 21:18.652
I just have
to pray for strength.

21:18.652 --> 21:20.487
It's here.

21:20.487 --> 21:22.573
You just have
to ask for it.

21:22.573 --> 21:24.158
It's not for me.

21:25.284 --> 21:26.911
It's for Elizabeth.

21:26.911 --> 21:29.080
She doesn't want me to go,

21:29.080 --> 21:31.498
but I don't have
a choice, Frank.

21:31.498 --> 21:34.668
I'm being called
to serve a greater purpose.

21:34.668 --> 21:36.670
FRANK:
There is a time
for every purpose,

21:36.670 --> 21:37.922
my friend.

21:37.922 --> 21:39.799
Then it's
that time for me.

21:43.094 --> 21:45.679
I've decided
to take the assignment.

21:47.890 --> 21:49.142
Jack.

21:51.936 --> 21:53.896
I'll leave
you two alone.

21:58.192 --> 22:01.195
[♪♪♪]

22:01.195 --> 22:02.947
I didn't know
that you had

22:02.947 --> 22:05.616
made up your mind
about going north.

22:05.616 --> 22:07.201
I started
to tell you before.

22:07.201 --> 22:08.577
I don't want you to go.

22:08.577 --> 22:10.288
Elizabeth, I...

22:10.288 --> 22:11.705
It's too dangerous.

22:11.705 --> 22:13.582
But it's
the right thing to do.

22:13.582 --> 22:15.584
You have to have faith
that it'll--

22:15.584 --> 22:17.170
How can you ask me
to have faith

22:17.170 --> 22:18.671
after what happened to Doug?

22:18.671 --> 22:20.173
Listen to me.

22:20.173 --> 22:23.176
The same God
that has called you to teach...

22:23.176 --> 22:26.344
to change
these children's lives...

22:27.513 --> 22:29.890
has called me
to serve my country.

22:32.268 --> 22:33.769
What about us?

22:33.769 --> 22:35.271
I'll come back.

22:35.271 --> 22:37.397
This is where my home is.

22:37.397 --> 22:39.399
It's where my heart is.

22:41.527 --> 22:43.904
But you know
as well as I do,

22:43.904 --> 22:47.533
that bad things happen
if good people do nothing.

22:49.409 --> 22:51.495
All right, then...

22:51.495 --> 22:53.371
I will go with you.

22:53.371 --> 22:55.249
You can't.
Why not?

22:55.249 --> 22:56.583
For a million reasons.

22:56.583 --> 22:57.543
Name one.

22:57.543 --> 22:58.878
You're needed here.

22:58.878 --> 23:00.921
Your destiny is
to teach these children,

23:00.921 --> 23:02.548
to change their lives.

23:02.548 --> 23:06.219
I can't take you away from that,
not even for a day.

23:08.346 --> 23:10.430
How long will you be gone?

23:11.724 --> 23:13.184
I don't know.

23:14.268 --> 23:15.936
It's an indefinite posting.

23:17.938 --> 23:20.066
[♪♪♪]

23:20.066 --> 23:21.067
[SOBS]

23:21.067 --> 23:22.693
Elizabeth!

23:25.154 --> 23:27.405
Elizabeth--
Let me go!

23:27.405 --> 23:29.533
Jack.
Just let me finish!

23:29.533 --> 23:31.244
You're my life.

23:31.244 --> 23:33.371
You're everything to me.

23:33.371 --> 23:35.289
[CRYING]
Jack, please,

23:35.289 --> 23:38.084
just leave me alone.

23:39.877 --> 23:42.380
[♪♪♪]

23:50.388 --> 23:53.057
[♪♪♪]

24:18.707 --> 24:20.876
You've always known that
Jack isn't the kind of man

24:20.876 --> 24:23.461
who can look the other way
when something needs to be done,

24:23.461 --> 24:25.714
no matter
what the sacrifice.

24:25.714 --> 24:28.675
It's one of the reasons
I love him so much.

24:31.553 --> 24:34.098
But it doesn't make...

24:34.098 --> 24:37.184
his leaving any easier.

24:37.184 --> 24:39.019
Of course it doesn't.

24:39.019 --> 24:41.814
I guess I knew
this might happen.

24:41.814 --> 24:43.274
[SIGHS]

24:43.274 --> 24:45.567
Ever since Doug died,

24:45.567 --> 24:48.862
I've seen how
it's torn him apart.

24:48.862 --> 24:50.948
I've seen it too.

24:50.948 --> 24:53.409
He's not the same.

24:53.409 --> 24:55.828
He says
he doesn't want to go,

24:55.828 --> 24:58.414
but that he has to go.

24:58.414 --> 25:00.416
Jack didn't choose this.

25:00.416 --> 25:03.210
He was chosen
to fight the good fight.

25:03.210 --> 25:05.421
[RESIGNED SIGH]

25:10.468 --> 25:12.761
I have to go talk to him.

25:14.138 --> 25:16.723
Jack came by earlier,

25:16.723 --> 25:18.516
before you got here.

25:18.516 --> 25:21.354
He wanted me
to give you this.

25:30.196 --> 25:32.448
"Take a walk with me."

25:38.329 --> 25:41.707
[♪♪♪]

26:36.345 --> 26:39.098
Is there a reason
for this walk?

26:39.098 --> 26:40.974
There is.

26:42.476 --> 26:44.311
Elizabeth...

26:44.311 --> 26:46.813
from the very first moment
we met,

26:46.813 --> 26:49.191
I knew heaven had sent
an angel into my life.

26:49.191 --> 26:51.569
I don't know when
I'm coming back,

26:51.569 --> 26:54.029
so I don't know if it's fair
to ask you to wait for me--

26:54.029 --> 26:55.197
Jack...

26:55.197 --> 26:58.451
I would wait
an eternity for you.

27:01.245 --> 27:03.872
[♪♪♪]

27:12.131 --> 27:13.466
[LAUGHS SHAKILY]

27:13.466 --> 27:15.217
Elizabeth Thatcher...

27:16.260 --> 27:17.761
will you marry me?

27:17.761 --> 27:19.096
[LAUGHS WHILE CRYING]

27:19.096 --> 27:21.223
Of course I will!
Yes!

27:21.223 --> 27:22.682
Yes!

27:22.682 --> 27:24.310
[SOBS HAPPILY]

27:38.031 --> 27:40.200
[♪♪♪]

27:42.202 --> 27:43.579
I love you.

27:43.579 --> 27:45.789
[WHISPERS]
I love you.

27:58.469 --> 28:00.346
[♪♪♪]

28:00.346 --> 28:02.264
Oh, Elizabeth!

28:02.264 --> 28:04.016
I'm just so happy
for you and Jack.

28:04.016 --> 28:06.143
The two of you
are adorable together.

28:06.143 --> 28:07.645
That's very
sweet of you.

28:07.645 --> 28:09.605
I should have known
this was going to happen,

28:09.605 --> 28:12.191
from the moment you caught
the bouquet at my wedding.

28:12.191 --> 28:13.609
It was meant to be!

28:13.609 --> 28:15.194
I just can't believe
he has to leave

28:15.194 --> 28:16.862
first thing
in the morning.

28:16.862 --> 28:19.031
Can't you convince him to stay
a little while longer

28:19.031 --> 28:21.992
so that I can throw you
a proper engagement party?

28:21.992 --> 28:23.410
Um...

28:23.410 --> 28:26.121
He doesn't have a choice,
Rosemary.

28:26.121 --> 28:27.665
Superintendent Collins
needs him

28:27.665 --> 28:28.999
as soon as he can pack.

28:28.999 --> 28:30.584
Oh, you poor dear.

28:30.584 --> 28:32.419
This must be so hard on you.

28:32.419 --> 28:34.380
It isn't easy.

28:34.380 --> 28:35.964
But on
the bright side,

28:35.964 --> 28:37.508
there'll be
a wedding to plan.

28:37.508 --> 28:40.052
Oh, my word.
That's right!

28:40.052 --> 28:42.012
You'll need someone
to take charge

28:42.012 --> 28:44.598
and make sure it is
the wedding of the century.

28:44.598 --> 28:47.100
Say no more.
Of course, I will do it!

28:47.100 --> 28:48.977
[GIGGLES]

28:48.977 --> 28:51.980
Uh, Rosemary,
why don't we give Elizabeth

28:51.980 --> 28:54.774
a moment to let everything
to sink in?

28:54.774 --> 28:57.819
She's dealing with
so much right now.

28:57.819 --> 28:59.071
Yes. Of course.

29:01.156 --> 29:03.450
BILL:
I know it wasn't
an easy decision, Jack.

29:03.450 --> 29:05.077
I respect you for it.

29:05.077 --> 29:06.036
We all do.

29:06.036 --> 29:07.371
I don't know when

29:07.371 --> 29:09.206
they're gonna
send another Mountie.

29:09.206 --> 29:10.290
Could be a while.

29:10.290 --> 29:12.000
Wouldn't surprise me.

29:12.000 --> 29:14.628
I'd like to appoint you
Acting Sheriff while I'm gone.

29:14.628 --> 29:16.088
Glad to do it.

29:16.088 --> 29:18.048
Well, Hope Valley's
in good hands, then.

29:19.966 --> 29:22.344
ABIGAIL:
Well, I think
it is time for a toast.

29:22.344 --> 29:23.679
Great idea.

29:23.679 --> 29:26.265
Everyone? Can I get
your attention, please?

29:26.265 --> 29:31.478
I would like to propose
a toast to the happy couple.

29:31.478 --> 29:34.898
Never in my life have I met
two people more in love

29:34.898 --> 29:37.192
than Jack Thornton
and Elizabeth Thatcher.

29:38.235 --> 29:39.737
To honor...

29:39.737 --> 29:41.238
to faith...

29:41.238 --> 29:43.240
to true love.

29:43.240 --> 29:44.824
Hear, hear.

29:44.824 --> 29:46.452
ALL:
Hear, hear.

29:48.537 --> 29:51.540
[♪♪♪]

30:01.717 --> 30:03.260
I don't want this to end.

30:03.260 --> 30:05.178
Neither do I...

30:07.847 --> 30:09.683
But I have to start packing.

30:12.269 --> 30:13.687
I'll find you later.

30:13.687 --> 30:15.272
Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm.

30:26.283 --> 30:28.160
Oh, Elizabeth.

30:30.370 --> 30:33.039
I don't know
if I should be happy or sad.

30:33.039 --> 30:36.335
I think it's safe
to say both.

30:38.295 --> 30:39.797
[WHISPERS]
It's okay.

30:45.051 --> 30:47.638
[RIP WHINING SOFTLY]

30:50.265 --> 30:51.767
Time has come, my friend.

30:51.767 --> 30:54.060
Bill's gonna look after you
till I get back,

30:54.060 --> 30:55.395
but there are a few things

30:55.395 --> 30:57.230
I'll need you to keep
an eye on for me.

30:58.524 --> 30:59.983
Firstly,

31:01.026 --> 31:02.736
there's Cody.

31:03.779 --> 31:05.447
Now, he's a good kid,

31:05.447 --> 31:08.408
but he's gonna need help
with that new dog of his.

31:09.702 --> 31:11.578
And then there's Elizabeth...

31:13.580 --> 31:15.332
[SIGHS]

31:17.376 --> 31:21.171
She is the sun and the moon
and the stars.

31:21.171 --> 31:23.423
Never forget that.

31:25.718 --> 31:27.886
I'm gonna miss you, buddy.

31:30.848 --> 31:33.475
[♪♪♪]

31:35.060 --> 31:37.312
LEE:
Rosie? Sweetheart?

31:37.312 --> 31:38.856
What's wrong?

31:38.856 --> 31:41.066
I can't sleep.

31:41.066 --> 31:43.819
I was thinking
about Jack.

31:43.819 --> 31:45.320
And Elizabeth.

31:46.405 --> 31:48.866
Hmm. You're not
the only one.

31:48.866 --> 31:51.535
What is she gonna do
when he's gone?

31:53.161 --> 31:55.121
What are we gonna do?

31:57.833 --> 32:00.126
I'm really gonna miss him.

32:00.126 --> 32:01.670
We all will.

32:01.670 --> 32:03.422
But we'll be fine.

32:03.422 --> 32:05.173
And so will Elizabeth.

32:06.633 --> 32:09.845
Hope Valley won't be
the same until he's back.

32:09.845 --> 32:11.513
No.

32:11.513 --> 32:13.557
No. It won't.

32:16.393 --> 32:18.270
Everything changes.

32:18.270 --> 32:19.979
I know that.

32:21.774 --> 32:24.610
But does it have
to change so fast?

32:26.986 --> 32:28.822
It's a little scary.

32:29.907 --> 32:33.034
Well, that's what
I'm here for...

32:35.788 --> 32:38.415
To make sure that
you're never afraid.

32:41.334 --> 32:43.670
And you're wrong,
you know?

32:43.670 --> 32:45.088
I am?
Mm-hmm.

32:45.088 --> 32:46.757
About what?

32:46.757 --> 32:48.884
Not everything changes.

32:50.427 --> 32:53.889
Some things never do
and never will.

32:53.889 --> 32:55.766
Name one.

32:57.016 --> 32:58.602
How much I love you.

32:58.602 --> 32:59.978
[CHUCKLES]

32:59.978 --> 33:02.355
[WHISPERS]
Do you promise?

33:06.526 --> 33:09.446
LEE:
Seems I already did.

33:32.845 --> 33:35.388
[♪♪♪]

34:00.956 --> 34:03.375
It's time.

34:15.637 --> 34:18.139
[♪♪♪]

34:23.395 --> 34:25.397
It's been an honor
to serve with you, Jack.

34:25.397 --> 34:27.106
Come home soon.

34:32.362 --> 34:34.531
[♪♪♪]

34:36.199 --> 34:38.451
You are such
a blessing, Abigail.

34:38.451 --> 34:40.537
[SOBBING]
Oh, Jack.

34:43.790 --> 34:45.291
Now, you take care of her.

34:45.291 --> 34:47.252
We're gonna miss you.

35:07.940 --> 35:09.482
I have to go.

35:09.482 --> 35:11.068
[WEAKLY]
I know.

35:23.288 --> 35:24.706
Mmm.

35:35.425 --> 35:38.344
[♪♪♪]

36:11.003 --> 36:13.588
[PANTING]

36:15.966 --> 36:17.759
[SHOUTS]
Jack!

36:19.260 --> 36:20.887
[SOBBING]

36:24.975 --> 36:27.435
[♪♪♪]

36:44.744 --> 36:48.498
[♪♪♪]

37:26.369 --> 37:28.371
ROSEMARY:
Oh, dear.
I do hope she comes.

37:28.371 --> 37:30.790
ABIGAIL:
Maybe we should
get started, just in case.

37:30.790 --> 37:32.792
ROSEMARY:
Uh...

37:32.792 --> 37:34.961
Ladies and gentlemen,
may I have your attention?

37:34.961 --> 37:36.337
Everyone,
take a seat, please.

37:36.337 --> 37:37.505
We're about to begin.

37:37.505 --> 37:39.091
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

37:39.091 --> 37:41.467
Now, it looks like
Miss Thatcher

37:41.467 --> 37:43.178
might not be able to make it,

37:43.178 --> 37:47.015
but we have a wonderful recital
planned for you.

37:47.015 --> 37:50.936
The program will begin with
our very own Bill Avery.

37:52.270 --> 37:53.605
[APPLAUDING]

37:53.605 --> 37:56.024
ROSEMARY:
Oh! And friends!

38:03.281 --> 38:05.283
[GUITAR PLAYING]

38:06.492 --> 38:09.246
♪ This little light of mine ♪

38:09.246 --> 38:11.831
♪ I'm gonna let it shine ♪

38:11.831 --> 38:13.332
Where's Miss Thatcher?

38:13.332 --> 38:15.043
She's feeling
under the weather, dear.

38:15.043 --> 38:17.129
But we were supposed
to do this together.

38:17.129 --> 38:19.338
I know.

38:19.338 --> 38:21.883
But she'd want you
to play anyway.

38:21.883 --> 38:23.384
She really would.

38:23.384 --> 38:26.763
♪ Let it shine
Let it shine, let it shine ♪

38:26.763 --> 38:28.223
One more!

38:28.223 --> 38:33.019
♪ Let it shine
Let it shine, let it shine ♪

38:34.062 --> 38:36.189
Way to go! Very good.

38:36.189 --> 38:38.191
[APPLAUDING]

38:44.447 --> 38:46.324
Wasn't that lovely?

38:46.324 --> 38:49.577
Oh, thank you, Bill--
And friends!

38:49.577 --> 38:53.331
And now our next performer
is Timmy Lawson.

38:53.331 --> 38:55.208
I can't.

38:57.460 --> 38:59.504
Of course you can,
sweetheart.

38:59.504 --> 39:00.964
Everyone here is your friend.

39:00.964 --> 39:02.548
No, I can't.

39:02.548 --> 39:03.800
Miss Thatcher promised

39:03.800 --> 39:06.011
she'd sing
while I played the piano.

39:06.011 --> 39:08.721
ELIZABETH:
And I never
break a promise.

39:11.599 --> 39:14.144
[♪♪♪]

39:19.107 --> 39:20.608
Come on.

39:20.608 --> 39:22.568
But I'm scared.

39:24.070 --> 39:26.031
Do it for Mountie Jack.

39:26.031 --> 39:27.991
It's his favorite, remember?

39:38.210 --> 39:40.837
[PIANO PLAYING]

39:45.217 --> 39:49.054
♪ Oh, Danny boy ♪

39:49.054 --> 39:54.267
♪ The pipes
The pipes are calling ♪

39:56.019 --> 39:59.981
♪ From glen to glen ♪

39:59.981 --> 40:05.695
♪ And down the mountain side ♪

40:08.531 --> 40:11.492
♪ The summer's gone ♪

40:11.492 --> 40:16.706
♪ And all the flowers
Are dying ♪

40:18.917 --> 40:22.503
♪ It's you
It's you ♪

40:22.503 --> 40:27.926
♪ Must go
And I must bide ♪

40:30.053 --> 40:33.973
♪ But come ye back ♪

40:33.973 --> 40:40.897
♪ When summer's in the meadow ♪

40:40.897 --> 40:46.361
♪ Or when the valley ♪

40:46.361 --> 40:52.951
♪ Is hushed
And white with snow ♪

40:52.951 --> 40:57.622
♪ And I'll be here ♪

40:57.622 --> 41:00.541
♪ In sunshine ♪

41:00.541 --> 41:05.504
♪ Or in shadow ♪

41:06.714 --> 41:09.384
♪ Oh, Danny boy ♪

41:10.468 --> 41:13.930
♪ Oh, Danny boy ♪

41:15.432 --> 41:18.393
♪ I love you so ♪

41:22.397 --> 41:24.774
[APPLAUSE]

41:26.609 --> 41:29.487
[♪♪♪]

41:56.973 --> 41:59.142
[♪♪♪]
